This paper deals with multi-modal image registration, which is a problem commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The approach taken in this paper involves training an image-to-image translation network, which is a common technique in the field of generative models (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which is a topic commonly studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data, which is a topic commonly studied in the multimedia (cs.MM) community.
